s, conflict with those of their employers, and reveal the barriers many face by being excluded from most statutory employment laws, sometimes in violation of the Canadian Charter of Rights and Freedoms. Contributors: Gianna Argento, Bob Barnetson, Michael J. Broadway, Jill Bucklaschuk, Delna Contractor, Darlene A. Dunlop, Brynna Hambly (Takasugi), Zane Hamm, Paul Kennett, Jennifer Koshan, C.F. Andrew Lau, J. Graham Martinelli, Shirley A. McDonald, Robin C. McIntyre, Nelson Medeiros, Kerry Preibisch, Heidi Rolfe, Patricia Tomic, Ricardo Trumper, and Kay Elizabeth Turner.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAgricultural laborersxLegal status, laws, etc.zCanada, Western. 0aAgricultural laborerszCanada, WesternxSocial conditions. 0aAgricultural laborers--Legal status, laws, etc.--Canada, Western. 0aAgricultural laws and legislationzCanada, Western. 7aLAW / Labor & Employment.2bisacsh  aAgriculture / Labour Laws.1 aArgento, Gianna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnetson, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarnetson, Bob, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBroadway, Michael J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBucklaschuk, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aContractor, Delna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDunlop, Darlene A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHambly (Takasugi), Brynna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHambly Takasugi, Brynna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHamm, Zane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKennett, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id